1
00:00:01,390 --> 00:00:05,030
Episode 12

2
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:12,880
What is she doing back here?

3
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:24,340
Ha Eun Ju, you didn't end up getting fired?

4
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:29,660
You are hanging on as the President's connection. Why ask me?

5
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,730
She's so crazy, really.

6
00:00:33,730 --> 00:00:37,690
Next time I will kill you with my own hands.

7
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:44,720
Are you alright?

8
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,780
Why don't you mind your own business?

9
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:50,410
Anyway, you're really amazing.

10
00:00:50,410 --> 00:00:54,020
I didn't expect you'd accept to move to that place for rehearsal.

11
00:00:54,020 --> 00:00:58,530
Stop right there.  It only feels bad when I hear a compliment from you.

12
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:06,950
Hong Yi Yeong, when you were a junior, did you take a class with me at Gyeongsang National University?

13
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:11,020
Something like Social Media Marketing...

14
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:13,300
Did that happen?

15
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:17,830
I think it's possible. But where are you asking, all of a sudden?

16
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:23,040
You can work on the test until noon.

17
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:28,130
If you are finished, leave the test answer sheet on the desk and leave.

18
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:32,000
Do you, by chance, remember that class' graduate assistant?

19
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,990
Graduate assistant?

20
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:39,390
I don't remember. Was there an assistant?

21
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:44,900
Never mind.  I don't have anything to talk to you about. Go.

22
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:48,100
What are you saying out of the blue?

23
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,520
Artists are also employees.

24
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:56,660
Rescind the wrongful dismissal.

25
00:01:56,660 --> 00:01:58,810
Conductor Nam must apologize.

26
00:01:58,810 --> 00:02:01,040
Sinyeong Philharmonic, reflect upon yourself.

27
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,320
Artists are also employees.

28
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,660
Rescind the wrongful dismissal.

29
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:10,360
As I live and breathe I never expected to see the Ministry of Labor come to do an audit.

30
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,960
Has the Chairwoman returned?

31
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,420
She comes back on the weekend.

32
00:02:13,420 --> 00:02:17,010
Is President Go still in on a rampage?

33
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:19,820
Don't even mention it. He calls several times daily.

34
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:24,100
I think he's going to pass all the blame to me.

35
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:27,460
Yes.  That's why you should have told the Board your side of the story first.

36
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:31,540
As I think about it, she joined the orchestra the same time as we did.

37
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:36,900
Gong Seong Min entered our orchestra during a dark period and suffered a lot.

38
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,820
Artists are also employees.

39
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:41,050
Rescind the wrongful dismissal.

40
00:02:41,050 --> 00:02:43,960
Conductor Nam must apologize.

41
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:49,100
If I am not reinstated, I'm going to city hall. I'll file a protest there.

42
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:56,720
Our orchestra has been running at a deficit for five years.

43
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,180
Don't lie.

44
00:02:58,180 --> 00:03:01,000
The whole world knows that Sinyeong Group supports our orchestra.

45
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,010
Our funding was reduced a while ago.

46
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:07,280
If things are left as they are now, we will all be unemployed.

47
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:10,430
They are supporting Maestro Nam. Our orchestra is begging to be saved.

48
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:15,230
I am sorry but I can't take your side.

49
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:26,800
Unni, please save us. Save us.  We are your colleagues.

50
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:44,070
Before that, let me ask you just one thing.

51
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:49,110
Did you also think my performance was worth only 40 points?

52
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,390
I sent your résumé to Professor Kang at Sinyeong Music College.

53
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:58,500
You could teach a few hours there.

54
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:01,200
I gave you a letter of recommendation.

55
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:16,760
I quit singing because of vocal chord nodules.

56
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:19,080
I can still do music even if I can't perform.

57
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:24,210
I thought I was going to die, but dying isn't easy.

58
00:04:25,650 --> 00:04:28,190
I've also been through it.

59
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:31,630
It's something even our juniors will have to suffer.  Someday.

60
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:58,100
Conductor, did you perhaps know that the dead Kim Ian had an older brother?

61
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,150
What are you talking about?

62
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:03,930
When I was at Gyeongsang University I took a liberal arts class with Hong Yi Yeong.

63
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:09,220
There was a graduate assistant.  He came once to proctor a test.

64
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:12,450
He also collected our homework on behalf of the professor.

65
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:14,920
What did that person have to do with Kim Ian?

66
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:18,900
I think he was Kim Ian's hyung.

67
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:21,900
Now, he is a member of our orchestra.

68
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:24,800
Come in.

69
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:30,200
Welcome. Coffee? I just made it.

70
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:33,930
No, I'm fine. What did you need?

71
00:05:33,930 --> 00:05:37,770
It's nothing important. I wanted to ask you a quick question.

72
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:42,800
I heard something strange yesterday. Jang Yun is not Jang Yun.

73
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:47,810
I looked up the résumé you submitted to the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

74
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:51,390
Besides your name is all the rest here phony?

75
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:52,930
No.

76
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:55,700
You know that falsifying documents like this is a crime, don't you?

77
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,830
I know.

78
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:03,090
Then, may I ask why you used a phony name when you joined the orchestra?

79
00:06:03,090 --> 00:06:07,570
No matter how much I think about it, I can't tell whether this is advantageous to you or not.

80
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:12,240
It's not as though you stole someone else's résumé. So why the hell did you do it?

81
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:16,020
I don't want to say anything. It's a very personal reason.

82
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:21,100
If you inform the orchestra and they fire me, I'll leave, no problem. You can go ahead and report it.

83
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:25,960
Is it possibly because you don't want someone to find out your true identity?

84
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:29,250
Just exactly who? For what reason?

85
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:32,190
You don't need to know.

86
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,830
I'm sorry! I'm sorry.

87
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:45,230
I understand you don't want the Sinyeong Philharmonic to know.

88
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:49,290
I'll take my time considering whether to report it or not.

89
00:06:49,290 --> 00:06:51,380
That's all for today. Leave.

90
00:07:13,470 --> 00:07:15,780
You scared me!

91
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:19,820
Why did the Conductor call you? You haven't done something wrong, have you?

92
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:23,280
Just... We were talking about the performance.

93
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,340
I was worried for nothing.

94
00:07:25,340 --> 00:07:28,060
One isn't usually called out for a good reason.

95
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:34,120
Do you remember the percussion practice room with the Colberg?

96
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:38,810
I was going to visit with you before but we didn't because you passed out.

97
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:41,360
Yes, I remember. Why?

98
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:45,010
Would you like to go with me tomorrow?  We are taking a break from rehearsals.

99
00:07:45,010 --> 00:07:47,150
Tomorrow?

100
00:07:47,910 --> 00:07:49,130
Why tomorrow?

101
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:50,550
Do you have plans?

102
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:56,000
It's not an important appointment, however I cannot cancel it.

103
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:00,260
If you decline to see a Colberg, it must be an important appointment. Well, just—

104
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:03,410
Never mind. There won't be a next time.

105
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:07,800
How can you be so heartless?

106
00:08:09,970 --> 00:08:11,060
Hello?

107
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:14,430
Ms. Hong Yi Yeong. Is six pm, by chance, a good time?

108
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:17,260
Let's have a lesson a little earlier.

109
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:19,820
This seems like the right place.

110
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:25,930
Hong Yi Yeong. Over here.

111
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:30,820
Is the practice room nearby?

112
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,970
Did you get lost on the way?

113
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:35,180
Yes, not really.

114
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,620
Are we not going to the practice room?

115
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:45,390
You're still a long way from entering the practice room.

116
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:49,730
Hold the mallet and stand there on tiptoe.

117
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,620
I'm sorry?

118
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:57,400
Don't make me repeat myself.  Stand firmly on your toes, keeping your heels up.

119
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:59,120
Oh. Yes.

120
00:09:04,530 --> 00:09:09,940
Up to your chin, down to your belly button. Hit a 120 bpm four-beat tempo equally with both arms. Start.

121
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:10,630
Excuse me?

122
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:13,430
A tempo of 120 bpm and a 4/4 beat.

123
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,940
Yes.

124
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:24,020
Loosen your shoulders. Don't bring your arms lower than your belly button.

125
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:25,990
8/8 beat.

126
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,660
16/16.

127
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:37,520
Increase the tempo. 130 beats per minute.

128
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:42,900
140.

129
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,320
150.

130
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:50,810
160.

131
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,560
170.

132
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,220
170.

133
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:56,590
170.

134
00:09:56,590 --> 00:10:00,400
I'm sorry. I nearly died.

135
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,760
Repeat everything from the beginning to now ten times.

136
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:04,550
What?

137
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:08,560
120 bpm 4/4 beat.

138
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,550
Yes sir.

139
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,420
I'm sorry I'm late.

140
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:20,330
How could you let the CEO wait like this?

141
00:10:20,330 --> 00:10:25,490
The Chairwoman isn't present. It's my first time meeting you too.

142
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:28,720
I'm sorry. The meeting ended very late.

143
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,900
I'm sorry.  I've been very rude when we are meeting for the first time.

144
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,160
Don't worry.

145
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:39,420
It was a last-minute meeting scheduled to suit me, so I should be flexible.

146
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:43,670
- Please bring another menu here.
- Yes.

147
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:46,720
- Have some wine.
- Yes.

148
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:52,170
We were talking and CEO Jang said that he is very interested in our art foundation.

149
00:10:52,170 --> 00:10:55,520
And he has a deep interest in classical music.

150
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,530
I've heard it often from the Chairwoman.

151
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:00,690
She said you're even a patron for many organizations.

152
00:11:00,690 --> 00:11:03,330
You're embarassing me.

153
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:08,020
Professor Kang told me you were very aggressive so I expected someone very scary.

154
00:11:08,020 --> 00:11:10,380
You aren't at all.

155
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,390
What I said is correct.

156
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:19,400
She looks like a flower, but our General Manager Yun is very scary. We must be careful.

157
00:11:19,410 --> 00:11:22,550
Especially when it comes to donations, you must be very careful.

158
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:28,800
I had hoped Maestro Nam would come with me today.  He suddenly had a flu fever.

159
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,010
Next time we will greet you together.

160
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:35,590
Don't worry about it. I'm here to meet you two today.

161
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:37,200
Cheers.

162
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,540
Ah, it hurts.

163
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:49,350
I'm sorry.

164
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:52,160
No, I just don't have strength in my arms.

165
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:54,370
Thank you.

166
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:58,560
It's no problem.

167
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:17,990
He's not home yet.

168
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,240
Yeah, Unni?

169
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:30,220
I had a lesson today, so I'm home late.

170
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:34,550
Yesterday I was acting a bit sensitive. You aren't mad at me, right?

171
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:38,670
If I got angry about something like that, I would die of stress.

172
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:41,250
Then, it's all good.

173
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:46,310
However... I really don't want you to be talking about the accident.

174
00:12:46,310 --> 00:12:49,930
Mom and Dad too. They said they were heartbroken after you left.

175
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:54,010
We have forgotten nearly everything and are getting over it.  Let's not dig out more details of that day.

176
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:55,570
That would be good for you too.

177
00:12:55,570 --> 00:12:57,570
Okay.

178
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,740
Are you prepared for your blind date?

179
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,610
Prepare what?

180
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:06,710
It's all because of you. Why did you have to hurt your leg?

181
00:13:06,710 --> 00:13:08,890
This is the first time I've been grateful for crutches.

182
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:11,920
You should try it out. It'd be good if he was a good person.

183
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:15,360
Forget it. I'm hanging up.

184
00:13:38,810 --> 00:13:41,490
What is this?

185
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:48,020
Did that jerk Jae Hyeong break in again?

186
00:13:57,430 --> 00:13:59,700
This fool!

187
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:05,180
Noona Yi Yeong

188
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:08,610
Why aren't you picking up? It keeps ringing, so it must be important.

189
00:14:08,610 --> 00:14:10,790
Forget it.

190
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:15,390
So, you had something you wanted to tell me?

191
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:21,260
What's this?

192
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:24,980
Are you perhaps afraid that your beloved cousin murdered someone?

193
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:34,200
When did you take this?

194
00:14:35,510 --> 00:14:37,770
Have you been following me?

195
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:39,690
Why would I be following you?

196
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:42,070
I took it coincidentally while I was waiting for Yi Yeong.

197
00:14:42,070 --> 00:14:43,940
So what about that picture did you want me to see?

198
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:45,980
I heard that day.

199
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:50,300
- Noona Su Yeong told you to keep away from Yi Yeong.
- And?

200
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:54,900
- Isn't there a reason that Noona Su Yeong was so angry?
- So what if there is?

201
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:59,060
This photo... can I show it to Yi Yeong?

202
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,060
Are you threatening me right now?

203
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:08,510
It's not a threat. I'm making a reasonable request.

204
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,700
From now on, keep away from Noona Yi Yeong!

205
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:14,760
You keep away! You, you—

206
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:18,000
Don't you recall what you did to her?

207
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,800
- A person can make a mistake at least once in their life.
- A mistake?

208
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:23,360
You don't make any mistakes, Hyung?

209
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:31,110
You get out of here. Don't look for me.

210
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:37,350
Noona Yi Yeong really is a good person.

211
00:15:38,530 --> 00:15:39,710
So what?

212
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:43,110
Even if I am young, I am good at reading people.

213
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:45,970
But in my eyes, you don't seem like a good guy.

214
00:15:45,970 --> 00:15:47,870
You seem like you would hurt her.

215
00:15:47,870 --> 00:15:52,160
Because of my mistake, I also hurt her, but her getting hurt again, because of you...

216
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,470
I don't want to see it, even on my death bed.

217
00:15:55,640 --> 00:16:01,000
Then you tell her yourself that I seem  like a bad guy.

218
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
And you show her this pic directly, alright?

219
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:08,300
This little kid.

220
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:21,410
Insomnia

221
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:24,090
You don't seem like a good guy in my eyes.

222
00:16:24,090 --> 00:16:27,370
You seem like you would hurt her.

223
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,200
Show some concern about how you dress.

224
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:41,740
Good luck. Don't be rude like your unni.

225
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:43,640
Don't worry.

226
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:46,710
I dressed myself up nice and will mind my manners too.

227
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:49,130
I won't swear.

228
00:16:55,670 --> 00:16:58,790
You said you had plans but...

229
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,330
you were going on a blind date?

230
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:08,210
Well, about that...

231
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:15,930
I ended having to go after fighting with my sister.

232
00:17:15,930 --> 00:17:22,220
You worked at getting ready.  You dressed in pretty clothing.

233
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:28,090
Can you walk down the stairs?

234
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:30,010
Of course.

235
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:49,540
What are you doing to do if you get hurt?

236
00:17:49,540 --> 00:17:52,010
Since you are going on a blind date and all.

237
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,750
Don't make fun of me, okay?

238
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:59,830
Are you in a teasing mood? I'm going to the blind date.

239
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:01,680
So what?

240
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,620
You really don't care that I'm going on a blind date?

241
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:10,130
The fact that I'm going on a blind date.

242
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:13,040
You know that I'm not going to tell you to not go.

243
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:16,370
If that is so, who is being calm? You're in a foul mood.

244
00:18:16,370 --> 00:18:18,390
So disappointing.

245
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:25,710
So should you just not go and spend some time with me?

246
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:30,090
There's is not even one drop of sincerity in your voice.

247
00:18:30,090 --> 00:18:32,650
Go exercise or something.

248
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:37,320
I'm being serious though...

249
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:42,930
♫ Darling you mean the whole wide world to me ♫

250
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:50,070
♫ Darling you are sweeter than an evergreen ♫

251
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:55,450
Yi Yeong, is there something wrong today?

252
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:57,920
Give me that photo.

253
